# Copy this file to `.dev.vars` (gitignored) and fill in real values locally.
# NO real secrets are committed to this template — only documented variable names.
#
# These are the RUNTIME Worker secrets the CMS reads. In production set each one with
# `wrangler secret put <NAME>` (never commit a real value, never add them to
# wrangler.jsonc). Leave every assignment empty here.
#
# ─── Required ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Better Auth signing secret. Auth init refuses to start and login returns 500
# without it. Must be >= 16 chars — generate with `openssl rand -hex 32`.
BETTER_AUTH_SECRET=
#
# JWT signing secret used pervasively by the layered JWT plugin (36 refs in the
# bundle). Set it — generate with `openssl rand -hex 32`.
JWT_SECRET=
#
# ─── Optional ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Public base URL of the CMS Worker. Only needed if Better Auth's base-URL
# autodetect fails (e.g. behind a proxy). Leave empty otherwise.
BETTER_AUTH_URL=
#
# Comma-separated exact origins allowed to call the CMS API cross-origin (no
# wildcard). Mirrors the `CORS_ORIGINS` var in wrangler.jsonc; filled in Phase 15/17.
CORS_ORIGINS=
#
# ─── NOT runtime secrets ────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# ADMIN_EMAIL / ADMIN_PASSWORD are SEED-TIME shell env for the one-shot admin seed
# (`pnpm seed`, Plan 14-03 / docs/cms.md) — NOT `wrangler secret put` runtime Worker
# secrets. Do not set real values here or in wrangler.jsonc.
